relation: You can use a UT EID to...
Submit test scores, high school transcripts, and an application to the university.
Submit a job application and resume to the university.
Register for classes, check grades, access online course information, pay for bills, etc.
Access payroll, benefit, and W-2 information, and use secure online services in UT Direct, etc.
Sign up for campus visits and use the eProxy system, etc.
Order transcripts, apply for re-admission, enroll in continuing and professional education.
Access business applications, such as the accounting system, post and receive job applications.
Become a library patron, participate in the University Interscholastic League, donate to the university, etc.
pageTitle: UT EID Help - Who needs a UT EID?

textBeforeTable: The UT EID is an electronic identifier - your "user name" with The University of Texas. If you are associated with the university or if you need to complete online transactions with the university, you need a UT EID. A UT EID is not necessary to access public information online, such as the UTNetCAT library catalog. Who needs a UT EID, and why? Help Topics Self-Service Tools UT EID Help Skip to main content
